<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mbeki Stresses Regional Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 17 (xinhua) -- Regional cooperation is not just
the responsibility of governments, South African President Thabo
Mbeki said Tuesday at the meeting marking the 19th birthday of the
Southern African Development Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
"It's the responsibility of both the government and the
people," said Mbeki.
</P>
<P>
The South African President, who currently chairs the regional
organization, agreed with his Mozambican counterpart Joaquim
Chissano that everybody should join hands in this common effort,
stressing that the southern African countries depend on one
another for development and progress.
</P>
<P>
"We have met to say South Africa cannot progress unless Lesotho
 progresses, that Botswana cannot progress unless South Africa
progresses," etc., he noted.
</P>
<P>
"It's the same for the Democratic Republic of the Congo, for
Zambia, for Tanzania, for Seychelles, for Mauritius, for
Swaziland, and for all the member states of SADC," he said.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state and government of SADC will meet Wednesday,
among other things, on further strengthening the regional bloc in
order to ensure that all the SADC member countries achieve peace,
progress and prosperity in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the idea of cooperation between the SADC and the
Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) forwarded by
honored guest Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo, Mbeki said
that "we will pay careful attention to the proposal."
</P>
<P>
He said measures will be taken for the cooperation between the
two sub- regions 
</P>
</TEXT>
