<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Writes off Zambian Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Germany has wrote off part of
Zambia's debt amounting to 384 billion Kwacha (about 153.6 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The period of payment of the remaining 407 billion Kwacha
Zambia owes Germany has been extended for 16 more years.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to the effect was signed here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After signing the agreement Zambian Finance Minister Katele
Kalumba said that the debt cancellation is a great contribution to
his country's economic development and will ease Zambian
government's budgetary external debt service obligation.
</P>
<P>
He said the government is paying greater attention to spending
funds in favor of economic infrastructure and poverty reduction
and urged the government departments to start putting in place
cost-serving measures such as the aggressive implementation of
public sector reform program.
</P>
<P>
Bernhard Zisese, Director of the Federal Ministry of Finance of
Germany, said after signing the agreement that the writing off of
Zambia's debt is part of the Neapel conditions that will see 67
percent of Zambia's debt cancelled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
