<HEADLINE> Iran Air Offers Discount for Exporting Carpets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 17 (Xinhua) -- In an effort to boost Iran's
non-oil exports, the country's flag carrier Iran Air is to cut
down by 15 percent air freight rates for hand-woven carpets and
air fares for passengers introduced by the Export Promotion Center.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA),
the discounts will be effective for two months until October 17
for both Iranian and foreign nationals.
</P>
<P>
Iran is famous for its hand-woven Persian carpets, whose craft
dates back more than one thousand years ago. It now accounts for
31 percent of the world trade of carpets.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said authorization for discounted rates will have to be
collected by each passenger or exporter at Iran's Export
Promotion Center in northern Tehran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
