<HEADLINE> Negotiations With Savimbi Impossible: Angolan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Jose Eduardo
Dos Santos Tuesday rejected the possibility of negotiating with
Jonas Savimbi, leader of the rebel National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
Civil war broke out again between government forces and UNITA
troops since December last year after the UNITA refused to
implement the 1994 Lusaka peace accord which ended the civil war
since 1975.
</P>
<P>
"Nothing for negotiating, ... but the Lusaka Protocol should be
 implemented," said Dos Santos in a speech at the Summit of the
Southern African Development Community (SADC), which opened
Tuesday in Maputo, the capital of Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The president added that above all, Savimbi's troops should be
disarmed in accordance with the protocol.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government and the rebel UNITA signed the Lusaka
Protocol in November,1994 in an effort to end the long-drawn-out
civil war, but Luanda declared it to be a failure in late 1998
when fighting renewed in Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
