<HEADLINE> Saudi Leaders Condole with Turkey on Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Saudi leaders on Tuesday
extended condolences over the deaths of more than 1,000 Turkish
people in the powerful earthquake that hit western Turkey earlier
in the day.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi Press Agency said that King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz
expressed his deepest condolence to the families of the victims.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that in a similar message to Turkish President
Suleyman Demirel, Saudi Crown Prince and Deputy Prime Minister
Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz also condoled over the victims of the
quake.
</P>
<P>
The devastating tremble, which measured 6.8 on the Richter
scale, demolished apartment buildings, trapping thousands under
tons of rubbles in western Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
