<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on Tuesday condoled
with his Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel upon the heavy loss
of lives in an earthquake.
</P>
<P>
In a cable sent to Demirel, Mubarak expressed condolences of
Egypt and the Egyptian people to the Turkish people, Egypt's
Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian leader voiced his country's readiness to offer any
assistance needed to the rescue and relief operations.
</P>
<P>
A powerful earthquake of magnitude 6.8 struck western Turkey in
the early hours of Tuesday, killing 1,400 people and injuring 6,000
others in Istanbul and at least four other cities.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel has decided to deliver emergency aid and
dispatch a medical team to Turkey whose western part was hit by a
strong earthquake in the early hours of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At least 1,400 people have been killed and more than 6,000
others injured in the earthquake.
</P>
<P>
Israeli President Ezer Weizman called his Turkish counterpart
Suleyman Demirel earlier in the day to express his sympathy with
the victims of the earthquake, which rocked western Turkey early
Tuesday morning, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Three transportation planes with emergency supply and a
medical and rescue team will leave for Turkey Tuesday evening,
according to the radio.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- More than 1,400 people have been killed and over
6,000 others injured in a powerful earthquake that struck Western
Turkey in the early hours of Tuesday, according to local media
reports.
</P>
<P>
The powerful quake with a magnitude of 7.8 occurred at 3:00
a.m. (0000 GMT). The epicenter is located at about 70 kilometers
southeast of Istanbul, near the bustling industrial city of
Izmit.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that 160 sailors were reported dead from the
collapse of two navy buildings in Golcuk, a town of 75,000
habitants.
</P>
<P>
The rescue workers are continuing sifting through piles of
rubble of the collapsed buildings in the tremor-hit cities for the
survivors and the bodies of the dead. And the injured is being
rushed to the nearby hospitals or treated in the sidewalks.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit and Interior Minister
Saadettin Tantan have gone to the sites to inspect the situation.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Nineteen Iraqi civilians were killed and 11 others
injured on Tuesday in attacks by U.S. and British warplanes on
residential areas and civilian facilities in northern and southern
Iraq, the Iraqi News Agency INA reported.
</P>
<P>
At 10:35 (0635 GMT) 11 formations of U.S. and British warplanes
coming from Turkish airspace violated northern Iraqi airspace over
Neineva, Erbil and Dohuk provinces, said an Iraqi military
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The fighter jets attacked some civilian and service facilities,
residential areas as well as military sites in the region, some
of the targets are not in the no-fly zone, killing eight civilians
and injuring nine others.
</P>
<P>
At 14:07 (1007 GMT) 12 formations of U.S. and British warplanes
coming from Saudi and Kuwaiti bases violated southern Iraqi
airspace over Basrah, Thi-Qar, Qadisiyah, Misan and Wasit
provinces, causing one injury.


17/08/99 19:53 GMT

NNNN
04:04 04:05 g # PAB
</P>
