<HEADLINE> Egypt Sends Relief to Turkish Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Egypt on Tuesday sent a plane load
of relief materials to Turkey in aid of victims in a devastating
earthquake hitting the west of the country.
</P>
<P>
Under directives of Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, Egypt's
armed forces collected medicines, medical and rescue equipment and
tents for the injured, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Another plane will carry more relief material, including
foodstuffs, to Turkey later in the day, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
A strong quake at a magnitude of 7.8 struck western Turkey in
the early hours of Tuesday, killing more than 1,000 people and
injuring over 5,000 others in Istanbul and at least four other
cities.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak has condoled with Turkish President Suleyman Demirel on
the heavy loss of lives in a cable and expressed readiness to
offer any assistance needed to the rescue and relief operations.
</P>
</TEXT>
