<HEADLINE> France Sends Rescuers to Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 17 (Xinhua) -- France sent 60 professional
rescuers to Turkey on Tuesday to participate in the rescue work,
after a strong earthquake killed 1,100 people and wounded 5,000 in
northwest Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The rescuers, including three doctors and accompanied by three
master searching dogs, belong to the Unit of Intervention of Civil
Security service of the Interior Ministry and are experts of
searching for people trapped in rubbles.
</P>
<P>
Led by Colonel Michel Bauchet-Canonne, they left Istres in
southern France on an Airbus plane and will rush to the scene of
the earthquake upon arrival in Istanbul, reported Agence
France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
Both French President Jacques Chirac and Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin have expressed their condolences to the Turkish government
for the numerous deaths in the earthquake.  
</P>
</TEXT>
