<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Inflation at 29-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 17 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's year-on-year
consumer inflation rate dropped to 4.9 percent in July, the lowest
since March 1970, Statistics South Africa announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The rate, as measured by the Consumer Price Index, was 2.4
percentage points lower than the corresponding annual rate of 7.3
percent recorded in June this year.
</P>
<P>
The agency explained that this decrease was mainly caused by a
relative decrease of three percent in the interest rates on
mortgage bonds as from July 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
