<HEADLINE> DPRK, U.S. Generals Holds Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Generals from the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and the United States failed on
Tuesday to reach agreement on starting contacts to demarcate a
maritime boundary on the sea off western Korea.
</P>
<P>
The meeting at the truce village of Panmunjom, the 10th general
officer meeting since the forum was created in June last year, was
proposed by the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
General Ri Chan Bok was the chief negotiator of the DPRK while
Major General Michael Dunn was representing the U.S. side, the
Korean Central News Agency (KCNA) said.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, the DPRK side insisted that the issue should
be negotiated only between itself and the United States, in
accordance with the truce and international laws.
</P>
<P>
Pyongyang also proposed the detail plans for the working level
talks: closed-door talks on the issue begin at Panmunjom in the
last ten days of August; the delegation of each side composes of
five to seven members and is headed by a senior-colonel officer;
South Korean officers could also be involved; the meetings would
take place every 10 days in principle.
</P>
<P>
But the U.S side repeated its stance that the DPRK should open
talks with South Korea on the issue under the Joint Military
Committee established in 1991. It also insisted the Northern Limit
Line, which was unilaterally set up by the U.S. side at the end of
the Korean War in 1953 and has never been recognized by Pyongyang,
serve as a practical border.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK charged the United States was trying to shirk its
responsibility for easing up the tension on the Korean peninsula
by insisting that the DPRK and South Korea talk directly on the
issue.
</P>
<P>
Pyongyang refused to accept South Korea as a dialogue partner,
dismissing Seoul as a "puppet" regime.
</P>
<P>
General Ri also urged the United States and South Korea to
immediately call off their on-going massive joint military
exercise codenamed "Ul ji Focus Lens", which the DPRK denounced as
"a war gamble targeting the North."
</P>
<P>
The 12-day joint exercise began on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
