<HEADLINE> UK's Inflation Remains Steady In July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The UK's underlying rate of
inflation fell by 0.4 percent in July at an annual rate of 2.2
percent, the Office of National Statistics (ONS) announced
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The figure, which excludes mortgage interest payments, was
still below the government's target of 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The headline inflation rate in July, however is 1.3 percent
unchanged from the previous month, despite the City predictions of
a slight fall.
</P>
<P>
So the ONS' figures likely to be seen as a warning that
inflationary pressures in the economy are rising more strongly
than had been thought.
</P>
<P>
As the UK economy is picking up speed, any threat of inflation
spoiling the government's aim of maintaining sustainable growth is
certain to lead to an early interest rate rise. 
</P>
