<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Host African TB Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Health officials from South
Africa and eleven other African states will meet in Pretoria
Thursday to discuss ways of tuberculosis (TB) control.
</P>
<P>
All twelve states attending the conference are recognized
internationally as "high TB burden countries", the department of
health said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
TB experts from the World Health Organization (WHO), the United
States Center for Disease Control and the World Bank are expected
to attend the three-day event.
</P>
<P>
WHO has identified South Africa and the other participating
countries as among those hardest hit by TB and HIV-related
diseases.
</P>
<P>
"The initiative aims to push TB control higher in the
international political agenda, expand international partners
working against TB, and set the stage for increased investment in
controlling TB," the department said in a statement. 
