who have been affected in some way, losing their homes or
belongings," he said. "We do not have all the information to say
exactly how many people are victims, but we need an estimate to
have funds as soon as possible."
</P>
<P>
He said tents, blankets, food and water purification tablets
would be the top priority.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Red Crescent, which sent four rescue and relief
teams to the zone, set up a field hospital in Yalova, south of
Izmit, according to the federation. 
