<HEADLINE> Bulgaria to Send Firemen to Help Quake-Hit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria will dispatch a team of
39 fire fighters to join the efforts to put down the quake-caused
fire in Turkish Izmit oil refinery.
</P>
<P>
The team is headed by Bulgarian Fire and Emergency Service
deputy director Col. Ljuben Neshkov.
</P>
<P>
Equipped with fire engines, rescue vehicles and heat-reflecting
and chemical-proof clothing, the firemen were dispatched in
response to the special request by Turkish government to handle
the situation at the oil refinery some 10 km from Izmit.
</P>
<P>
A Bulgarian Red Cross rescue team of nine with four sniffer
dogs are currently working in Istanbul. They are among the first
foreign teams having arrived in Turkey to clear debris and rescue
survivors. Austria, Germany, the Netherlands, Russia, Israel and
Azerbaijan have also sent rescue teams, the Bulgarian Foreign
Ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
