<DOCNO> XIE19990818.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Receive 20m Dollar Grant from Denmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive a
140-million Danish kroner (about 20.2 million U.S. dollars) grant
from Denmark for rural development activities in two coastal
districts, the national news agency BSS reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement in this regard, signed here Wednesday, is for the
implementation of the phase-2 of the rural development project,
under which infrastructure development in the southern coastal
districts of Barguna and Patuakhali began in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Denmark gave 710 million taka (about 14.3 million
dollars) for the phase-1 of the project, thus raising the total
grant for the project to 1.71 billion taka (about 34.5 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The objective of the project is to support the economic and
social development of the region by rehabilitation of markets and
roads in the area.
</P>
<P>
In the first phase of the project, roads and markets have been
improved in eight of the 11 sub-districts of the two districts,
and the phase-2 will cover the remaining three sub-districts.
</P>
</TEXT>
