<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
the diplomatic news released by Xinhua today:
</P>
<P>
 Malaysian PM Visits China
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Prime Minister Datuk Seri Mahathir bin Mohamad
arrived in the Chinese capital this afternoon for a three-day
working visit at the invitation of Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir's 100-odd entourage, including his wife Hasmah Benti
Haji Mohd Ali, high-ranking governmental officials and journalists,
also arrived aboard the same plane.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and Mahathir bin Mohamad held talks
at the Great Hall of the People here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Zhu welcomed Mahathir on his fifth visit to China, saying China
highly values the efforts Mahathir has made over the years to
promote the friendship and relations of cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the bilateral ties have witnessed smooth growth since
China and Malaysia forged diplomatic relations 25 years ago on the
basis of equality, mutual trust and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
"The two sides have carried out a series of cooperation with
substantial contents and tangible results," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The joint statement signed not long ago by foreign ministers of
the two countries on future bilateral cooperation framework not
only reviewed and confirmed the development of bilateral relations
but also mapped out a blueprint for the future cooperation, the
Chinese leader said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out that China values the status of Malaysia and
its role, cherishes the traditional friendship between the two
countries, and is willing to join Malaysia in further enhancing
cooperation in various fields in the hope that the two countries
become good-neighbors, good friends and good partners forever.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said that he had visited China several times. "I saw
China's progress and changes in each of my visit," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the prime minister, his current visit has two
missions: one is to celebrate the 25th anniversary of the
establishment of diplomatic ties between Malaysia and China and
the other is to further promote the development of the bilateral
relationship.
</P>
<P>
He said Malaysia will continue to adhere to the "one China"
policy. Also, he expressed the appreciation for China's agreement
in principle to sign a protocol pact on the nuclear-weapon-free-
zone status of southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
He once again expressed his appreciation for China's
responsible attitude during the Asia financial crisis and its
adherence to not devaluing the Chinese currency.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of government are satisfied with the growth of
trade and economic cooperation and exchanged views on furthering
such cooperation during the talks.
</P>
<P>
The two countries agreed to initiate a joint project on
starting a pulp mill as early as possible.
</P>
</TEXT>
