<HEADLINE> Escalated Fighting Leaves 21 Dead in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Defense Ministry
said on Wednesday government troops had killed six Tamil rebels in
fresh clashes in the north while 15 members of the security forces
were said to be killed in ambushes.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement that government troops on
Tuesday killed six rebels in three separate clashes in the
northern Wanni region.
</P>
<P>
However, military officials said Tamil rebels carried out fresh
attacks on government forces Wednesday killing 15 policemen and
soldiers and wounding five others.
</P>
<P>
They said nine soldiers were killed Wednesday afternoon in a
claymore mine attack by the separatist Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) in the northern village of Navavi in the Wanni
region.
</P>
<P>
Six police commandos were shot dead when their patrol was
ambushed by Tamil rebels at the coastal village of Karaitivu, some
225 kilometers east of Colombo, officials said, adding five others
were wounded.
</P>
<P>
The attacks followed a series of attacks in the island's north
and east where the LTTE rebels are fighting a 16-year-old war for
the establishment of an independent Tamil homeland.
</P>
<P>
Last week the LTTE ambushed a police convoy in the eastern
district of Batticaloa, killing 11 policemen. 
</P>
