<HEADLINE> Ericsson Invests in China's Mobile-Phone Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Ericsson Corporation
plans to collaborate with Guangdong Telecom Co. Ltd. in south
China's Guangdong Province to expand the Chinese company's global
mobile phone system.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed recently, the Swedish
telecommunications equipment maker will provide Guangdong Telecom
telecommunications with equipment worth 80 million U.S. dollars to
upgrade its facilities and services beginning this November.
</P>
<P>
By the time the project is completed, the telecom company's
mobile-phone system will be capable of serving 8 million users in
Guangdong, which has had one of the fast economic growth in the
country and now has 5 million mobile-phone subscribers.
</P>
<P>
Ericsson's cooperation with Guangdong Telecom began in 1987,
and the company now has 23 representative offices and eight joint
ventures in China, employing more than 3,800 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
