<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Second Highest Tunnel Road Opens in China's Highland Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The world's second highest tunnel
road on Daban Mountain 3,800 meters above sea level opened to
traffic today in China's northwest Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
The mountain, capped with snow for half the year on the Qinghai-
Tibet Plateau, is very steep, and in the past road traffic had to
be halted during the winter. With the 1,530-meter-long tunnel now
opened to traffic, the national highway running through it will be
open year round.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the tunnel began in August 1995, and was
completed at a a cost of 156 million yuan. This is China's first
tunnel built in the frigid zone, according to officials with the
provincial communications department.
</P>
<P>
The project used domestic technology and overseas management
experise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
