<HEADLINE> 5 People Killed in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mogadishu, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The killing for clan related
retaliations and banditry still continues at a very high rate
despite peace making efforts by some local Islamic courts.
</P>
<P>
At least five people were killed and six others wounded over
the past two days.
</P>
<P>
Nur Osman Jeyteh, a well known comedian and an actor, was
killed Tuesday. Together with his colleagues and a musical band,
he was going for a wedding ceremony when the gunmen intercepted
their bus and forced Jeyteh to get down and they shot him on the
spot.
</P>
<P>
He was among the five people killed. The reason for the killing
is not stated officially, however it is known that militiamen
from his Wa'aysleh subclan had killed earlier a man from the
Warsangeli subclan who Tuesday in their turn had killed Jeyleh for
retaliation purpose. 
</P>
