<HEADLINE> Chinese TV Viewers Favor "Princess Huanzhu" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Zhao Wei, who plays in "
Princess Huanzhu", was named best female lead at the 17th China
Gold-Eagle Awards at a ceremony held today in Shenzhen in south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Gold-Eagle Awards are directly selected by TV viewers. Zhao
Wei won by receiving 401,249 votes. "Princess Huanzhu" also
pocketed the top prize for long TV dramas by gaining 330,000 votes.
</P>
<P>
"Princess Huanzhu", which tells the story of a legendary
princess of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911), is one of the most
popular TV serials in China, and is currently broadcast by many
local TV stations.
</P>
<P>
The mood of nostalgia for imperial times seems dominant among
Chinese TV viewers this year as "Emperor Yongzheng," another long
drama about the Qing Dynasty, took eight top prizes including best
male lead which went to Tang Guoqiang, who plays the emperor.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizer of the awards, 625 TV dramas
contested for 123 awards and over 1.41 million votes were cast by
viewers.
</P>
<P>
The award ceremony was sponsored by TCL, a Chinese electronics
giant. 
</P>
