<HEADLINE> Chinese Capital Boosting Farm Products Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the national capital of
China, established a special organization, known as the "Green
Bridge Service Center", to promote the city's exports of farm
products.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Mayor Yue Fuhong said that the center aims to help up
enterprises specially engaged in production, sale, transport and
trade of farm goods, in accordance with international conventions.
</P>
<P>
The center will coordinate among its member enterprises,
provide information and train personnel, while trying to deal with
problems related to exports of their products.
</P>
<P>
So far, the center has had 72 members.
</P>
<P>
