<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Religious Official Analyzes Falun Gong Cult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- China's top official in charge
of religious affairs said on a popular TV talk show today that the
Falun Gong created by Li Hongzhi has all the features of a cult.
</P>
<P>
"A cult is characterized by cheating, madness, fallacy,
secretive organizations and activities, and anti-government and
anti-social motivations," Ye Xiaowen, director of State
Administration of Religious Affairs, told CCTV.
</P>
<P>
"And Falun Gong possess all these features," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that Li Hongzhi is more sophisticated than
most cult leaders because they designate a certain day as doomsday,
and when that doesn't happen, their preaching is self-destroyed.
</P>
<P>
"But Li Hongzhi differed by saying that the earth would have
exploded, but that he personally delayed the catastrophe for
another 30 years, so that he could have enough time to do whatever
he wants," the official said.
</P>
<P>
Ye justified the government's efforts to crack down on Falun
Gong as necessary to "protect the safety of citizens and their
property and to maintain social stability."
</P>
<P>
He said, however, that "common practitioners should be treated
with sympathy, care and help, because they are the victims of Li
Hongzhi," adding that even the organizers, given that they were
manipulated and deceived, should be warmly embraced by the
government and society once they repent.
</P>
<P>
Ye also stressed that respect for freedom of belief does not
contradict the Party and the government's propagation of atheism.
</P>
<P>
"Respecting freedom of belief does not in any way mean
providing soil for the growth of superstition or cults, and China'
s religious circles understand this too," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
