<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Providing Services for Telecom Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China signed a contract today with East Communications Co.
Ltd. (ECC) to set up a capital settlement network linking the
company's 32 sales outlets nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Yang Kaisheng, vice-governor of the bank, said here today that
this service is expected to help ECC improve its efficiency in the
use of capital.
</P>
<P>
He said that by using the network, all income brought in
through the company's sales outlets will reach the company's bank
accounts within two hours.
</P>
<P>
Prior to this, ECC's local settlements had to be accumulated at
its headquarters here by using the postal services, which usually
took seven or eight days.
</P>
<P>
ECC is China's largest listed telecommunications company, with
assets of two billion yuan. Its sales target for this year has
been set at 10 billion yuan, nearly double last year's record of 5.
5 billion yuan. 
</P>
