<HEADLINE> Imports of Disease-Contacted Livestock Banned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Early this month, China banned
all imports of cloven-footed animals from several countries which
were stricken by contagious animal diseases.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Botswana was hit by African hog cholera, Croatia by
classic hog cholera, and Zimbabwe and Peru by foot-and-mouth
disease, according to a notice released by the State
Administration for Entry-Exit Inspection and Quarantine of China.
</P>
<P>
In order to prevent the diseases from entering China, and to
protect China's animal husbandry, it was decided to ban imports of
pigs, wild boar, and related products from Botswana and Croatia,
and pigs, cows, sheep, other cloven-footed animals, and related
products from Zimbabwe and Peru, the notice said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
