<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Russia expressed on Wednesday its
concern over the allegedly Washington's attempt to derail the
Russian-Turkish "Blue Flood" gas pipeline project.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued by the Foreign Ministry, Moscow said it
has reliable information about political and other pressure
mounted by certain U.S. officials to try to block the project.
</P>
<P>
Moscow is especially worried by allegations that supplies of
Russian fuel products may undermine political and economic
independence of the countries involved, the Interfax news agency
quoted the statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ministry would like Russia's partners to refrain from using
such underhanded techniques as it runs counter to the generally
accepted principles of free trade, ethics of maintaining business
relations and the nature of Russian-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
Russia and the United States are on the same wavelength about
the need for economic efficiency and the comprehensive application
of ecological and international legal standards, which are the
main criteria in the evaluation of projects to expand the oil and
gas delivery infrastructure of the Caspian and Black Sea regions,
the statement said. 
