<HEADLINE> CSE General Index Reaches New All-time High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Shares on the Cyprus Stock
Exchange (CSE) Wednesday continued their rally, pushing the
General Index to a new all-time high.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the Index reached its third consecutive all-time
high just after the CSE week-long closure, as it went up by 0.7
percent to 326.93, the Cyprus News Agency (CNA) reported
</P>
<P>
The closure had been decided by the CSE Board in order to give
dealers time to clear up a backlog of paperwork caused by huge
trading volumes over the last weeks.
</P>
<P>
The volume of transactions fell to 28.4 million Cyprus pounds
(52.5 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's 33.6 million pounds
(62.2 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Last year, the average daily volume of transactions was 1.4
million pounds (2.8 million dollars) while for July 1999, it
reached 20 million pounds (37 million dollars). 
</P>
