<HEADLINE> China's Eximbank New Efforts to Boost Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The export of biological
engineering, new materials and other new and high-tech products
will enjoy priority in using credit from the Export and Import
Bank of China (Eximbank), according to sources from the Eximbank.
</P>
<P>
President of Eximbank Yang Zilin said that his bank has
designed nine new steps in a bid to meet the growing financing
demand of the country's export.
</P>
<P>
He said the implementation of the new steps will help increase
policy financial support for the export of machinery, electronics
products and complete sets of equipment.
</P>
<P>
The bank will further step up its financing support to the
export of key industries, key districts, key enterprises and key
projects, with priority given to the export of new and high-tech
products.
</P>
<P>
Support to small enterprises and small projects will also be
increased, he said. Closed-end loans will be granted to State-
owned large and medium-sized enterprises with temporary losses but
have orders to guarantee the repayment.
</P>
<P>
Overseas assembling projects using materials from China will
also be backed by the Eximbank, he said, with focus on light
industry, textiles, family appliances and other industries with
equipment and technological advantages.
</P>
<P>
In light of difficulties in obtaining credit guarantees, the
Eximbank is also considering granting no-guarantee loans to credit
worthy conglomerates with good financial situation.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that to make full use of overseas capital and to
facilitate the implementation of the country's active fiscal
policy and industrial policies, the his bank will give priority to
transportation, environmental protection, forestry and water
conservation projects, as well as the central and western areas of
the country in loans from foreign governments in the latter half
of the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
