<HEADLINE> Beijing Police Raid on Brothels, Prostitutes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Police sources announced today
that they detained more than 400 prostitutes and whorehouse
customers during a recent raid in preparation for activities to
mark the 50th founding anniversary of the People's Republic on
October 1.
</P>
<P>
Some 6,000 sauna rooms and beauty parlors that had provided
erotic and other illegal services to customers have been closed or
fined, sources said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, some 420,000 illegal books and VCDs, including 145,
000 carrying pornographic materials, have been confiscated, they
added.
</P>
<P>
Police confirmed that this was part of an intensified campaign
targeting all crimes in the Chinese capital before the gala
celebrations, featuring mass parades and military reviews at the
Tiananmen Square.
</P>
<P>
Sources revealed that police have arrested some 2,000 suspects
in nearly 1,000 cases in the past months, and smashed 139 criminal
rings.
</P>
<P>
More than 28,000 unlicensed buildings have been demolished to
make thoroughfares and streets more beautiful, and 100,000 people
without Beijing residential cards have been persuaded to move out
of the city.  
</P>
