<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Officials on Cross-Straits Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A three-day conference of
Chinese officials in charge of Taiwan affairs ended here today
after heated and in-depth discussions about Lee Teng-hui's "two-
state" remarks.
</P>
<P>
It was pointed out at the national conference of heads of
offices of Taiwan affairs that the "two-state" remarks have fully
exposed Lee Teng-hui's ambition to split the motherland, and has
enraged Chinese people both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The "two-state" claim could jeopardize Taiwan's social and
economic development, and hurt the immediate interests of Taiwan
compatriots, the conference warned.
</P>
<P>
"The assertion not only destroys the foundation of political
dialogue and negotiations between the two sides of the Taiwan
Straits, but also goes against the will of most people on the
island."
</P>
<P>
The conference stressed the importance of adhering to the "One
Country, Two Systems" principle and Chinese President Jiang Zemin'
s eight-point proposition on the Taiwan issue, and warned Lee Teng-
hui and the Taiwan authorities not to underestimate the firm
resolve of the Chinese government to safeguard state sovereignty,
dignity and territorial integrity, or the courage and strength of
the Chinese people to fight against separation.
</P>
<P>
Those attending the conference said that they would do their
utmost to realize the reunification through peaceful means and
vowed not to give up the use of force.
</P>
<P>
They said that Lee Teng-hui deceives the people of Taiwan by
saying he intends to go on with reunification negotiations without
recanting his "two-state" and "special state-to-state relations"
remarks, and they called on the Taiwan authorities to openly
abandon those remarks and return to the "One China" principle as
soon as possible.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
