<HEADLINE> China, Malaysia Sign Three Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Related departments of China and
Malaysia signed three documents here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and Malaysian Prime Minister Mohamad
Mahathir attended the signing ceremonies after they held talks in
the Great Hall of the People in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Academy of Sciences and the Chinese Academy of
Engineering Sciences respectively signed a memorandum with
Malaysia's Academy of Sciences on cooperation in science,
engineering and technology.
</P>
<P>
The third document was an agreement on the joint development of
forest land and the construction of pulp mills. 
</P>
