<HEADLINE> Key Index Rises in Karachi Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The 100-share price Index of
Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE) recorded an increase of 1.44 percent
Wednesday on short covering in blue chips by domestic investors,
dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The index surged 17.35 points to close at 1,218.45 with a
trading volume of 129.3 million shares as compared to 135.5
million shares on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Although the stock market had a depressed outlook, short
covering in blue chips supported the index," said a leading stock
broker.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 216 traded scrips, share prices of 110 scrips
registered gains while 42 sustained losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
