<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed higher in
Tokyo for the eighth straight trading day Wednesday, supported by
Tuesday's surge on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange edged up 32.17 points, or 0.18
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 17,892.26.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, rose 4.29 points or 0.29 percent to 1,478.43.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 501.86 million
shares from 387.00 million shares Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
After hitting the day's high of 18,082.47 in the morning, the
Nikkei index lost its upward momentum and fell to as low as 17,827.
89 in afternoon trading due to market concerns that its recent
rise was too rapid, a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
The key market gauge topped the 18,000 line for the first time
since July 22, when it touched 18,221.07 before closing at 17,730.
34.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers far exceeded
gainers 769 to 394 despite the overall rise in the Nikkei index,
with 150 issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
