<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
rebounded Wednesday as investors took heart in the release of
benign consumer price data in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index surged 38.0 points to close
at 3026.0, down from its intra-day high of 3036.7 points.
</P>
<P>
On the local bourse, the all industrials index rallied 68.4
points to 5192.9 and the all resources index climbed 13.1 points
to 1347.4 points.
</P>
<P>
Banking stocks were mostly firmer with the industry sub-index
gaining 14.2 points to 6281.5 as National Australia Bank added 17
cents to 23.57 Australian dollars, Westpac firmed 10 cents to
10.03 Australian dollars and ANZ strengthened five cents to 10.35
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth shed 64.9 cents, or 2.7 percent, to 23.351
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
There was a national turnover of 411.36 million stocks traded
for 1.2 billion Australian dollars (792 million U.S. dollars).
Rising stocks outnumbered falling stocks 705 to 548 and 410 stocks
remained steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
