<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar headed
lower Wednesday after the Reserve Bank of Australia signaled that
official interest rates would remain on hold.
</P>
<P>
The local unit finished the day at 64.72 U.S. cents from 64.89
at Tuesday's close, trading between 64.68 and 65.12 during the
session.
</P>
<P>
The central bank's report in its August Bulletin was
interpreted as signaling interest rates on hold, reducing demand
for Australian currency among offshore investors.
</P>
<P>
Also at the local close the Australian dollar was buying 0.6161
euro from 0.6141 at Tuesday's close and 73.43 Japanese yen from
74.31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
