<HEADLINE> Tennis Legends to Show in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Tennis-legends-filled Cathay
Pacific Champions, a new Asian Tennis Federation championship
event, will be staged from November 3 to 7 in Hong Kong Convention
and Exhibition Center, it was announced here on Wednesday by the
tournament organizer.
</P>
<P>
The event will draw fans of all ages with a notable line-up of
tennis "legends" including 11-time grand slam title-holder Bjorn
Borg, four-time US Open winner John McEnroe, seven-time grand slam
winner Mats Wilander and one-time French Open champion Yannick
Noah, Mansour Bahrami, Henri Leconte, Mikhail Pernfors and Peter
McNamara.
</P>
<P>
Between them, these players have collected a stunning 41 grand
slam single and double titles.
</P>
<P>
The eight renowned players will compete in the round robin
singles in two groups of four. The top two players of each group
will proceed to the semifinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
