systems" principle among the people of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Publicity of the successful implementation of the "one country,
two systems" in Hong Kong will help increase Taiwan people's
awareness of the principle, noted the members during a visit to
the One Country Two Systems Research Institute in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Shiu Sin-por, executive director of the institute, said Hong
Kong goes well under the "one country, two systems" principle, and
there is no significant change after the return of Hong Kong to
China.
</P>
<P>
Some people of Taiwan hope to maintain their current lifestyle,
and the "one country, two systems" principle is the very
expression of their wish, said Chyung-en Wu, president of the "
Alliance for the Reunification of China."
</P>
<P>
Wu said people on both sides across the Taiwan Straits should
have common understanding on the basis of "one China," and
everything can be discussed under the "one China" principle.
</P>
<P>
Different from Germany, China's sovereignty has never separated,
and Lee Teng-hui's "two states" theory is totally groundless, said
Wu.
</P>
<P>
The 22-member Taiwan delegation arrived in Hong Kong Tuesday,
following their visit to Beijing and Shanghai. Delegation members
returned to Taiwan in the afternoon. 
</P>
