<HEADLINE> Malaysia Launches Cyber Book Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A website known as the
Cyber Book Bank was launched Wednesday in Malaysia for
institutions and individuals planning to inform the public of
their intention to donate reading materials.
</P>
<P>
The Cyber Book Bank, a database which contains information on
reading materials or publications available for donation, was
launched here in conjunction with the "Reading Month" program
launched by Education Minister Najib Tun Razak a week ago.
</P>
<P>
This is an in-community effort by the Malaysian Public Library
Directors Council (PPAM).
</P>
