<HEADLINE> France, UK Stage Joint Operation Against Illegal Immigration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Police of France and Britain are
staging an intensive joint operation against illegal immigration
toward Britain.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted police sources as saying on
Wednesday that the primary phase of the operation is aimed at
controlling the flow of illegal immigrants to the northern area of
France, as well as at some railway stations of Paris, which serve
as a springboard for crossing the English Channel.
</P>
<P>
The immigration law of Britain is more tolerant than that of
France, especially in the field of political asylum.
</P>
<P>
Many immigrants from Algeria, Albania, Romania, Afghanistan,
Sri Lanka and Iraq are trying to take advantage of the wave of
sympathetic feelings for refugees after the war of Kosovo, to seek
political asylum in Britain, said police.
</P>
<P>
French police and customs officials are increasing control of
identity of foreigners on board trains and ferry boats.
</P>
<P>
Police said that some Mafia groups in Europe and other
countries could be running an underground immigration business.
</P>
</TEXT>
