<HEADLINE> Martial Arts Festival Opens In East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 18 (Xinhua)-- The Fourth Jinan International
Martial Arts Festival opened at the capital of east China's
Shandong Province today.
</P>
<P>
One hundred and forty-eight foreign contestants from 12
countries, including Canada, Argentina and France, and 62 Chinese
players will compete during the six-day festival.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has been one of the major places where Chinese martial
arts, or Wushu, originates. The province's Qufu City is where the
great Chinese thinker and educator Confucius was born about 2,500
years ago, while another city, Weifang, is known for kites.
