<HEADLINE> Vietnam Speeds Up Construction of Flood Control Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is boosting
infrastructural construction for agriculture, especially the
construction of irrigation projects for flood control.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government invested more than 1,854 billion
Vietnamese dong (132.4 million U.S. dollars) in infrastructural
construction for agriculture in the first seven months of 1999,
accounting for 77.8 percent of the yearly plan, according to a
report of the Vietnam News Agency on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The sum was disbursed in construction of irrigation projects.
</P>
<P>
Nine of 11 irrigation projects for flood control have been
fulfilled as scheduled, and judged as up to the standards of the
flood diversion projects.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government will invest an additional 640 billion
Vietnamese dong (45.7 million U.S. dollars) in building irrigation
projects in the remaining period of this year. Vietnam's Ministry
of Agriculture and Rural Development has assigned relevant
agencies to build these projects.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam had overfulfilled the plan on building infrastructural
projects for irrigation, agriculture, forestry and rural
development in 1998 by 12 percent with a total investment capital
of 2,488 billion Vietnamese dong (180 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government is focusing its limited capital on
key projects with a view to raising efficiency. Vietnam's
construction sector speeded up the construction of key flood
control projects and completed 51 projects, including 35
irrigation ones in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
