<HEADLINE> Chinese Swimmers Leave for Pan Pacific Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- World runner-up Zeng Qiliang,
together with three Chinese swimmers, left today for the Pan
Pacific Championships slated for August 19-29 in Sydney, Australia.
</P>
<P>
The five-member Chinese squad, including three males and two
females, divided into two groups as Zeng Qiliang, who won the
silver medal in the men's 100 meters breaststroke at the World
Swimming Championships in Perths, will first show up in the Pan
Pacific Championships.
</P>
<P>
Xie Xufeng, Chinese national medley champion, will take part in
the men's 200m individual medley and 200m butterfly, Li Wei will
have women's 100m breaststroke.
</P>
<P>
Pang Ran, a Beijing native teenager, who won the silver in the
women's 200m butterfly and a bronze medal from the 100m butterfly
at the World University Games in Palma, Spain last month, aims to
qualify for the 100 meters Olympic standard set by FINA, world
swimming governing body.
</P>
<P>
According to the 10-day Pan Pacific Championships schedule, Fu
Yong, number 4 in the men's 200m backstroke on the world rankings,
will arrive at Sydney later to compete in the 200m event.
</P>
<P>
"We hope veterans Zeng and Fu bring win at the championships
while the youngsters splash personal-bests and try to reach the
Olympic standard, " said Shi Tianshu, top official of the Chinese
Swimming Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
