<HEADLINE> Leading Titanium Producer Opens Stock Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 18 (Xinhua) -- China's only high-tech enterprise
featuring titanium research and production, Baoji Non-Ferrous
Metal Processing Plant (BNFMPP), set up a stock company recently
in Baoji, a leading industrial center in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The stock company, Baoji Titanium Stock Company Ltd., is
composed of six companies and universities in Shaanxi with the
approval of the State Economic and Trade Commission.
</P>
<P>
It will integrate scientific research with production and trade
and concentrate on developing rare metal and compound metallic
materials and dealing import and export of titanium-related
products, raw materials and equipment.
</P>
<P>
The company will issue A shares to fund technical upgrading of
existing titanium melting and processing systems.
</P>
<P>
The BNFMPP is the largest titanium-based rare metal production
center in China. Its products have been widely used in the fields
of space, aviation, chemistry, metallurgy, medicine and marine
projects.
</P>
<P>
Over 30 kinds of BNFMPP's products have obtained ISO9002
certificate and similar certificates of the United States, France
and Britain. The company pledged to raise its world market share
from the present two percent to 8-10 percent in upcoming years.
</P>
</TEXT>
