<DOCNO> XIE19990818.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Ethnic Games Opens on Auspicious Note </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- With the Ode of Good Luck
reverberating over the venue, the Sixth National Ethnic Games
opens in a folk way here, adding another note of jubilation to the
Tibet Autonomous Region (TAG) which was celebrating its 40th
anniversary of the Democratic Reform.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetans, who are for the first time to host such sport
gala of minority nationalities, has regarded the games as an
auspicious omen for the future development.
</P>
<P>
"The staging of such event will bring great boon to the whole
TAG, we have took it as a harbinger of a more promising future.
That is why we have put the ode to Good Luck as the theme of the
opening ceremony," said Dan Zen Gongbu, the general masterminder
for the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The TAG have witnessed substantial changes since 1959 when the
Democratic Reform was innovated, abolishing the system of
exploitation and separating religion from government.
</P>
<P>
About 1,200 children holding balloons flooded in the stadium
from all directions before they formed a shape of the five rings
of Olympics, raising the curtain of the grand ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The stands immediately turned into a sea of white Hada (Tibetan
's traditional silk stripe to show hospitality) as the spectators
flourished hundreds of thousands of Hada and formed a Mexico Wave.
</P>
<P>
Tibetan culture began to take center stage when the Tibetan
folk songs and dances, which has strong sense of rhythm, impressed
the whole spectators so much that even the locals could not but
reveal their surprises.
</P>
<P>
"It is the first spectacular scene I have ever seen, even we
locals haven't expected such depth of dances with strong flavor of
Tibetan culture," said Duoji Cairang, who works in the TAG
Theatrical Company. "it has become the town's talk since the
opening ceremony rehearsal was held three days in advance."
</P>
<P>
Against the blue sky and green grass, about 7,000 Tibetans from
the countryside and the grazing area, with a large variety of
hairstyles and dressings, danced to show their wishes for
beautiful life and express their happiness about harvest.
</P>
<P>
The folk songs were so impressive that the spectators were
brought back to ancient times when the Tibetans lived a simple
life on grazing and farming, then the rhythm became intense,
reminiscent of the scene when the locals struggled with natural
hardship for better livelihood, before it became light and quick,
showing a picture of Tibetans enjoying their happy lives.
</P>
<P>
Xiangbala (the Utopia of the Tibetans) Is Not Remote was the
song which touched the heartstrings of the whole stadium as the
local famous singer Dege Medo toured the stadium on a Mercedes-
benz car to push the opening ceremony to a new high.
</P>
<P>
The diversity of the performances also impressed the foreign
visitors deeply. Adriana Williams, together with her other six
fellows, has come to the Tibet Plateau for the second time and
they heaped their praises on the ceremony and the TAG.
</P>
<P>
"We came here both for sightseeing and having a look at the
national ethnic games," said Williams who came from California of
the United States. "The performances are really wonderful,
fantastic."
</P>
<P>
"The livelihood here is getting better and better, and in the
west we have often been told all is bad here, but after we came
here, it is not really that way, it is not all bad."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
