<HEADLINE> Four Cypriots Arrested for Possession of Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' anti-drug officers
discovered three kilograms of hashish in a car they stopped on a
street in Nicosia Monday night, a newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Four Cypriots appeared Tuesday before Nicosia District Court in
connection with the seizure, the Cyprus Mail said.
</P>
<P>
Two of them, 35-year-old Alecos Ioannou and 31-year-old Savvas
Loizou, were in the car when it was stopped by the police.
</P>
<P>
The other two suspects, 21-year-old Loukas Kyriacou and
39-year-old Charalambos Hadjimarkou, were arrested shortly after
the drugs were found inside the passenger seat of the car.
</P>
<P>
Police said drug squad officers intercepted the car after
receiving a tip-off and placing the vehicle under surveillance.
</P>
<P>
Kyriacou had a small quantity of hashish on him when he was
arrested and Loizou later handed over 120 grams of the drug to
officers, police said.
</P>
<P>
In Larnaca meanwhile, the District Court fined two touring
British social workers 300 Cyprus pounds (550 U.S. dollars) each
for possession and use of hashish. 
