<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Round Up Over 60,000 Fugitives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police, in the latest
endeavor against fugitives, have so far captured more than 60,000
escaped prisoners and criminal suspects, according to a source
from the Ministry of Public Security here today.
</P>
<P>
The nationwide drive kicked off on July 1 by the Ministry of
Public Security (MPS) to "eliminate any possible trouble and
create a still better environment for the celebrations of the 50th
founding anniversary of new China, and for the return of Macao to
the motherland," said a ministry official.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry has set up an information network to provide
police units nationwide with detailed information on the fugitives
in an effort to help increase the drive's effectiveness, the
official said, adding that of the total, some 37,000 criminal
suspects have been seized with the help of the network.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, ten policemen from Shanxi and
Liaoning provinces and Ningxia and Inner Mongolia autonomous
regions were wounded in the drive. A policeman named Xiao Fengming
in Jilin Province, northeast Chin, laid down his life in the
pursuit of a fugitive wanted by the Public Security Ministry.
</P>
</TEXT>
