<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Tea Production Declines 19 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 18 (Xinhua) -- India's tea production dropped
by 19 percent in the first half of 1999 to 261.2 million kilograms
against 322.1 million kg recorded a year ago, according to the
United Planters Association of South India (UPASI) .
</P>
<P>
Production has been hit mainly by poor harvest in the
northeast, which was affected by a prolonged dry spell and failure
of pre-monsoon showers.
</P>
<P>
In the northeast, production decreased to 167.6 million kg
during January-June this year against 219 million kg recorded a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
In view of the fall in production, the India Tea Association
has projected tea harvest to decline to 835 million kg this year
against 868.2 million kg in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that the global tea production has shown a
decline of nearly 100 million kg mainly due to fall in India's
harvest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990818.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Goodwill Winter Games to be Held in New York in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The first Goodwill Winter
Games will be held in Lake Placid, New York, from February 17 to
20, according to a local report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Lake Placid has staged the 1932 and 1980 Winter Olympics, but
some of its competition sites suffered from disuse and lack of
funding.
</P>
<P>
Among the improvements is a state-of-art luge, bobsled and
skeleton track slated to open in December. The upgrades and Lake
Placid's Olympic legacy helped convince Turner Broadcasting to
come to upstate New York for the first winter Goodwill Games.
</P>
<P>
The Summer Goodwill Games have been held four times. The Turner
formula invites world class athletes in a final-one format for
prize money. Training takes place on February 15.
</P>
<P>
In addition to bobsled, luge and skeleton, the games will
feature Alpine, cross-country and freestyle skiing, figure skating,
Nordic combined, short-track speedskating, ski jumping and
snowboarding.
</P>
<P>
Turner Broadcasting, the sponsor of the games, plans 16 hours
of television coverage on TNT network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
