<HEADLINE> Seeds On and Off Second Day of du Maurier Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The second day of the du Maurier
Open women's tennis tournament turned out a winning beginning for
top seed Martina Hingis of Switzerland, who dispatched American
Corina Morariu 6-0 and 6-3 Tuesday at Toronto's National Tennis
Centre.
</P>
<P>
She will meet 16th-seeded Chanda Rubin of the U.S. in the third
round of the event of 1.05 million U.S. dollars, reports available
here said.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, third-seeded Mary Pierce of France and sixth-
seeded Amanda Coetzer of South Africa advanced to the third round
after first round byes.
</P>
<P>
Pierce upset Ruxandra Dragomir of Romania 7-6 and 6-3 while
Coetzer defeated fellow Joannette Kruger 6-1 and 6-2.
</P>
<P>
No.16 Chanda Rubin of the U.S. also advanced to the third round
with a 6-2, 4-6, 6-4 victory over Nathalie Dechy of France.
</P>
<P>
Anne-Gaelle Sidot of France won over 17th-seeded Amy Frazier of
the U.S.. Sonya Jeyaseelan of Toronto lost her first-round match 7-
5, 6-2 to Japan's Ai Sugiyama, leaving Canada's top player Mareen
Drake and countrywoman Renata Kolbovic the only Canadians in the
tournament.
</P>
<P>
American Monica Seles will meet with Russian qualifier Tatiana
Panova in a second-round match Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Drake's second-round opponent will be the tournament's 15th
seed Elena Likehovtseva of Russia. 
</P>
