MEXICO CITY -- Mexico received 20 million overseas visitors and
its tourism revenue reached 8 billion U.S. dollars in 1998,
surpassing that of petroleum exports for the first time, Mexico's
Secretary of Tourism Oscar Espinosa said on Tuesday in Guatemala.
</P>
