<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Price Monitoring Committee Formed in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government has
formed a Price Monitoring Committee (PMC) to curb malpractice of
businessmen and to ensure that the implementation of value-added
tax (VAT) will not inflate prices, The Kathmandu Post reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The PMC is chaired by the finance secretary, home secretary,
supply secretary, the joint secretary at the Revenue Division and
the director-general of the VAT Department.
</P>
<P>
The committee is responsible for creating an environment for
controlling price hikes in the name of VAT and taking necessary
action in case of VAT collection on tax-free goods or by a
non-registered individual.
</P>
<P>
The PMC will also be formed at the district level.
</P>
<P>
VAT went into full enforcement Tuesday after nearly two years
of confusion over it. It is feared that the price of commodities
will rise with the implementation of VAT. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990818.0271 </DOCNO>
