<HEADLINE> 30 Fire Cases Reported in Myanmar in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and six
others injured in 30 fires which broke out in Myanmar in June, but
the number of fires was 11 cases less than in the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The fires also destroyed 69 houses, leaving 311 people
homeless, evening newspaper the City News reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the total fires, 26 cases or 83.87 percent were due to
negligence or were kitchen fires, it said, giving no details of
the property losses during the month.
</P>
<P>
The authorities have been maintaining fire prevention measures
in the entire country even during the five-month-long rainy
season which started in June.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, 453 fire cases occurred in
Myanmar in the first half of this year, destroying 1,710 houses,
killing 18 people and leaving 7,236 homeless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
