<HEADLINE> Prime Minister Says Yugoslavians to Rebuild Homeland on Their Own </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav Prime Minister Momir
Bulatovic told the Federal Assembly on Tuesday that the Yugoslav
people are confident of their own strength to rebuild homeland
despite the serious economic damage inflicted by NATO's savage
bombing.
</P>
<P>
Bulatovic said the Yugoslav people cherish no illusion that the
U.S.-led Western aggressors, who launched the most destructive
bombing against Yugoslavia, will help in the reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
They have bravely started the reconstruction process with their
own strength and are determined to carry through the work to its
completion. They will never sit back and wait for aid, but are
going all out to lift their nation out of its plight, Bulatovic
said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the NATO bombing has caused severe casualties and
a 20 percent decline in the Gross National Product (GNP) of
Yugoslavia. 
