<HEADLINE> Taiwan Investment in South China Keeps Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Investment from Taiwan
businesspeople has kept pouring into this southern Chinese
province of Guangdong since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Information from the provincial office for Taiwan affairs
revealed that Guangdong is home to 11,000 businesses funded by
Taiwan businessmen, with investment fields ranging from
petrochemical, iron and steel, bio-engineering industries to
computer development.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan investors have pumped in over seven billion U.S. dollars
of investment into the province, according to the information.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 of the total Taiwan-backed businesses were added
in the first six months of this year, with contracts involving
investment of well over one billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Grace T.H.W. Group, a plastic products maker from Taiwan, is
hoping to set up the world's largest production center of plastic
products in this capital of Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Corporate sources said that the conglomerate has been operating
four businesses in Guangzhou since 1996 when it first set foot in
this south Chinese city.
</P>
<P>
Construction of workshops and equipment installation for two
new businesses of the group has been carried out. Upon completion
of the two projects, the group's investment will climb to 640
million U.S. dollars and it will become the biggest Taiwan
investor in Guangdong Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
