<HEADLINE> China Restricts VCD, Refrigerator, Air Conditioner Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua)-- The State Economic and Trade
Commission will not approve any new project which produces VCD
players, refrigerators, air conditioners and some other products
to curb redundant production since September 1.
</P>
<P>
Also affected will be projects concerning thin plastic bags,
bicycles, microwave ovens, toothpaste, candy, salt, apple juice,
liquor and alcohol, according to the commission's recent
announcement.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, construction of luxury hotels, apartments and office
buildings as well as department stores which have not gained
government approval will also be halted.
</P>
<P>
New supermarkets and warehousing markets, which are the latest
mode of retail sales, will not be affected by the curb, the
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
Observers said that there has been a glutter of these products
and that in the area of VCD players, producers have resorted to
malicious competition by slashing prices drastically for survival.
</P>
</TEXT>
