<HEADLINE> Building Materials Sector Picks Up in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The quality of China's building
materials products sharply improved with the qualification ratio
approaching 90 percent in the first half of this year, according
to the State Administration of Building Materials Industry.
</P>
<P>
The ratio between production and marketing in the building
materials sector turned better in the January-June period and
exceeded that of the national average. Earnings from the sector
picked up month by month and exports grew briskly in the same
period, said an official from the administration.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that since the very beginning of this year,
China has supported the development of large building materials
enterprises, and has given priority to improving industrial
structure and developing new building materials, quality cement
and plate glass urgently needed by the national economy.
</P>
<P>
He said that the fast development in the construction of
infrastructure facilities and houses this year has effectively
boosted the growth of the main building materials.
</P>
<P>
He expects the country's annual cement and plate glass outputs
to reach 490 million tons and 160 million weight cases,
respectively, which will basically meet the needs in the sectors
of construction, automobiles and real estate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
