economic take-off in the early 21st century, according to a new
development program being worked out by the Ministry of
Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Under this program, technological contributions to the growth
of agricultural production will be increased from the current 42
percent to at least 55 percent by 2005 and more than 60 percent by
2015.
</P>
