<HEADLINE> Mexico, Cuba to Cooperate More Closely on Science, Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Mexico and Cuba agreed to
work together more closely on science and technology as they
concluded a two-day preparatory meeting here Tuesday for their
Mixed Commission of Development Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Delegations from the two countries vowed to begin "a new stage"
in bilateral relations with "renovated impetus" in the cooperation
in science and technology fields, the Mexican Foreign Ministry
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
An act was signed to define the projects of cooperation, which
involves sectors of environment, agriculture, livestock, fishing,
energy, health, social security, communication and transport.
</P>
<P>
Mexican Ambassador to Cuba Jorge Alberto Lozoya, who led the
Mexican delegation, said the cooperation with Cuba "is one of the
most diversified and systematic which Mexico maintains."
</P>
<P>
Cuban Vice-Minister of Foreign Investment Raul Taladrid, who
led the Cuban delegation, praised the "fruitful cooperation"
between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
