<HEADLINE> Cambodian PM Praises China's Foreign Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun
Sen praised China's foreign policy of non-interference in other
country's internal affairs and reiterated Cambodia's "one China"
policy.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister made the remarks during an exclusive
interview with Kyodo News, which was broadcast by Phnom Penh Radio
Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said he knew the attitude of Chinese leaders not to
influence and intervene in other country's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen, meanwhile, reaffirmed Cambodia's "one China" policy,
saying, "I follow the policy of our King that is the policy of one
China, whereas Taiwan is only a province of China."
</P>
<P>
"Some attempted to reopen a Taiwan office in Phnom Penh, but
they could not receive Hun Sen's support," he added. 
</P>
