<HEADLINE> Timberwolves Agree to Terms with Forward Joe Smith </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Joe Smith, the top overall
selection in the 1995 draft who was rejuvenated by a new
environment last season, today agreed to terms to remain with the
Minnesota Timberwolves.
</P>
<P>
Specifics of the deal were undisclosed. Smith's agent, Eric
Fleisher, who also represents Timberwolves superstar forward Kevin
Garnett, was unavailable for comment.
</P>
<P>
The Wolves also re-signed forward Tom Hammonds to an
undisclosed deal. The ninth overall pick in the 1989 draft
averaged 4.3 points and 2.8 rebounds last season, his second with
Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
Smith, 225 pounds, took the place of former All-Star Tom
Gugliotta last season, joining his third team in four years by
signing as a free agent. He teamed with Garnett for 149 blocked
shots in the lockout-abbreviated campaign.
</P>
<P>
"Joe and KG really complement each other and give us two of the
best shot-blocking forwards in the game today," Timberwolves
general manager and coach Flip Saunders said.
</P>
<P>
Smith, 24, averaged a career-low 13.7 points and 8.2 rebounds
in 43 games last season. Those numbers dropped to 7.5 and 6.5 in
four postseason games as Minnesota fell to the eventual champion
San Antonio Spurs in the first round. His scoring has dropped off
each of the last three years.
</P>
<P>
"We are extremely excited to re-sign Joe," Saunders said. "He
was able to re-establish himself in the shortened season last year
and we look for him to continue to grow with us."
</P>
<P>
Smith earned All-Rookie First Team honors after leaving
university. He averaged 15.3 points and 8.7 rebounds in 82 games.
</P>
</TEXT>
