<HEADLINE> URGENT: Earthquake Jolts Northern California </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake
measuring 5.0 on the Richter scale shook the Northern Californian
town of Bolinas, about 30 kilometers north of San Francisco, the
Associate Press reported.
</P>
<P>
