<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Divorce Rate Reaches New High in Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic has one of the
highest divorce rates in the world, according to official
statistics released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The divorce rate reached 58.8 percent last year, the highest in
the country's history and up by 20.2 percent compared with a
decade ago, the State Statistical Bureau said.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, 55,027 couples were married and 32,363 couples were
divorced. The population of the Czech Republic in the same year
was 10,289,600.
</P>
<P>
Czech experts say that in addition to personal trauma suffered
by divorced couples and their children, a high divorce rate also
affects the country's social stability.
</P>
<P>
The Czech authorities issued a new marriage law last August,
making it more difficult to divorce. In the fourth quarter last
year, 4,715 Czech couples were divorced, half the number in the
previous quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
