<HEADLINE> China's Largest Sweet Corn Processing Line into Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The largest sweet corn
processing line in China has been put into production at the
Xinzhou Economic Development Zone, in north China's Shanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The factory, with a total investment of 19.88 million yuan (
about 2.4 million US dollars) from a catering development company
in Shanxi, occupies an area of 10,000 sq m. Its key machinery has
been designed and manufactured by well-known machinery producers
in Germany and Japan, as well as China.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that the factory has now become the largest
sweet corn processor with the most advanced technology in China.
Its main products include vacuum-packed, quick-frozen fresh sweet
corn ears and quick-frozen sweet corn. And the annual output of
the vacuum-packed products is expected to reach 10 million, with a
sales volume worth 37.19 million yuan and yielding taxes of 9.37
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Xinzhou is a major corn-producing area in the province. The
sowing area for corn has been expanding with the restructuring of
the rural economy. The local sweet corn features high nutrition,
good taste and high protein due to the peculiar climate and other
natural conditions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local officials said that the area will try to raise
the added value of agricultural products by making good use of its
advantages in natural resources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
