<HEADLINE> Chongqing Aims to Improve Ecological Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- This municipality in southwest
China has drawn up a 50-year construction program to improve its
ecological environment, local officials said today.
</P>
<P>
In line with the program, Chongqing, an old industrial city
which consumes a great amount of high-sulfur coal, will increase
its forest coverage rate from the present 21 percent to 45 percent
by the year 2050, and its nature reserve area will account for 10
percent of its total area.
</P>
<P>
By then, the city's area afflicted by water and soil erosion,
which accounts for half of the city's total area, will be brought
under control.
</P>
<P>
The project is estimated to cost 58.6 billion yuan (about seven
billion U.S. dollars), with half of the funds coming from the
central government, and the rest to be raised by issuing shares
and bonds, and attracting foreign funds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
