<HEADLINE> Kuerten, Moya Advance to Third Round at RCA Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Former French Open champion
Gustavo Kuerten and Carlos Moya recorded second-round victories
with varying degrees of difficulty today at the $745,000 RCA
Championships hard court tennis event in Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten, the third-seeded Brazilian, disposed of Sjeng Schalken
of the Netherlands 6-4, 6-2. The fourth-seeded Moya needed eight
match points before outlasting Czech Daniel Vacek 1-6, 6-4, 7-6 (8-
6).
</P>
<P>
Eighth seed Thomas Johansson of Sweden, who claimed his first
Super 9 title at the du Maurier Open two weeks ago, was upset by
Arnaud Clement of France 6-3, 6-2. Fifteenth seed Francisco Clavet
of Spain joined Johansson on the sidelines after he was beaten by
Canada's Daniel Nestor 7-6 (7-1), 6-1 in a first-round match.
</P>
<P>
Also, Magnus Larsson swept past 1997 champion Jonas Bjorkman 6-
4, 7-6 (7-4) in an all-Swidish first-round battle; Andrei Pavel of
Romania topped American Chris Woodruff 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
No. 10 Thomas Enqvist of Sweden, No. 11 Nicolas Lapentti of
Ecuador, No. 12 Albert Costa of Spain and No. 14 Cedric Pioline of
Rance all won their opening-round matches on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Top seed and world No. 1 Pete Sampras of the United States will
put his 22-match winning streak on the line Wednesday against
Frenchman Guillaume Raoux in a second-round match. 
</P>
