<HEADLINE> U.S. Returns 14 Illegal Immigrants to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Navy Coast Guard boat on
Tuesday returned to Cuba 14 illegal immigrants who tried to land
in the United States by three fragile rafts.
</P>
<P>
The raft people, 13 men and one woman, were received by the
Havana port of Orozco, said the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The United States has so far returned 2,415 Cubans to the
Caribbean island through the port of Orozco and 422 through the U.
S. Naval Base of Guantanamo, 910 kilometers southeast of the Cuban
capital.
</P>
<P>
Cuba and the United States have signed an agreement under which
the United States returns any Cuban illegal immigrant found off
the U.S. coast. 
