<HEADLINE> Colombia, Panama Sign Security Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Colombia and Panama
signed an agreement on border security on Tuesday to help
strengthen bilateral ties and fight against drugs and arms
trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The document, the Operational Act between the Navy of the
Colombian Republic and the National Maritime Service of the
Republic of Panama, was signed by Colombian Commander of the
National Armada, Admiral Sergio Garcia Torres, and Panama's
Minister of Government and Justice Mariela del Carmen Sagel.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the navies of the two countries will
intensify their cooperation to combat trafficking in drugs,
illegal chemicals, weapons and munitions, in their respective
jurisdictions.
</P>
<P>
The document seeks to strengthen frontier and maritime security.
An Operational Working Committee has been set up to give
continuity to the agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
