<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military World Games Conclude in Zagreb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The Second Military
World Games concluded in the Croatian capital Zagreb on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The "Torch of Peace" which had been burning for the past ten
days was put off at the Maksimir Stadium.
</P>
<P>
In this biggest international multi-sport event held here,
about 4,500 athletes competed in 24 different sports as 81
countries and regions sent their delegations.
</P>
<P>
Russia topped the gold medals table with 45 golds while China
finished as runner-up with 29. Italy was third with 17 golds.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 world military records were broken at these games,
mostly from swimming and athletics.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's soccer final, Egypt beat Greece 5-4 in the penalty
shoot-outs after two sides tied 3-3 in 120 minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
