<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Displays Strength as China Rises in Military Sports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
By sportswriter Cao Li
</P>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia is undisputably the
biggest winner at the 2nd Military World Games here while China
doubled its gold medals as compared to last edition.
</P>
<P>
Russia snatched 45 gold medals to atop the medals tally while
China was second with 29 golds, 21 silvers and 15 bronzes in these
games organized by the International Military Sports Council (CISM)
.
</P>
<P>
The Russians were the competitors to be reckoned with in almost
every sport and had extra strength in combat sports such as judo,
wrestling and boxing, and swimming.
</P>
<P>
China, third placer on medals table with 13 golds at last games
in Rome, moved one place up to be the runner-up. Italy dropped to
the third place from second, finishing with 17 golds here.
</P>
<P>
China dominated the women's events in swimming, winning six
golds, seven silvers and one bronze.
</P>
<P>
Qi Hui became the most decorated swimmer by pocketing three
golds and one silver.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 CISM world records fell here, including two from
the battlefield of the military pentathlon.
</P>
<P>
Han Hye Gyong of DPR Korea broke the world record for the women
's obstacle running while her compatriot Myong Gum Sun shattered
grenade throwing mark.
</P>
<P>
Both previous records were set by the defending champions China,
who were dethroned here by DPR Korea in both the individual and
the team competition.
</P>
<P>
But China saved its face by winning the women's relay event
while its men retained individual and team titles.
</P>
<P>
This second edition of the Military World Games was no doubt a
boost of confidence for the International Military Sports Council
(CISM), which had not hosted a multi-sport event before 1995.
</P>
<P>
"The success at these games is an important step forward after
the start of the major sports event in Rome four years ago," said
CISM President Gianni Gola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
