<DOCNO> XIE19990818.0339 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Signs Military Construction Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
signed an 8.4-billion-U.S.-dollar spending bill Tuesday to
underwrite new military construction.
</P>
<P>
The Military Construction Appropriations Act pays for "the vast
majority" of his requested military construction projects and
housing program, Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
"The requested projects are critical to supporting military
readiness and the quality of life of our soldiers and their
families," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, Clinton criticized legislators for providing 93 million
dollars less than he requested for a chemical weapons
decommissioning program and adding 301 million dollars for 40
projects the Pentagon did not list as priorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
